	<b>Risk, Issue and Defect </b></td>
</tr>

    <tr>

      
      <td class="txt">
<br>These terms are most commonly confused with each other although they have entirely different meaning, audience and time of occurrence.
<br>
<br>
<br>Issue is something that we need to deal with at the current time. It is usually high level and generally non-technical in nature. E.g. Lack of resources, lack of skills.
<br>
<br>
<br>Risk is a potential disruptive event that may or may not occur in future. E.g. possible attrition during the project
<br>
<br>Risk is an possible event which has a potential to adversely affect your plans. Impact of a risk can be Positive (Opportunities) or Negative (Threats) on the project.
<br>
<br>
<br>Defect on the other hand is generally low level and technical in nature. E.g. Application throws an error when certain page is viewed.
